You need to update `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/app/tranquility/page.tsx`. Read it first, then apply ALL of the following changes:

**Fix 1 — Use OmegaMessage component instead of raw divs**
- Add import: `import OmegaMessage from '@/components/MessageBubble/OmegaMessage';`
- Add import: `import ThinkingIndicator from '@/components/MessageBubble/ThinkingIndicator';`  
- In the messages map, replace the omega message div:
  ```jsx
  // OLD:
  <div key={i} className={`${s.msg} ${msg.role === 'user' ? s.msgUser : s.msgOmega}`}>
    {msg.role === 'omega' && <span className={s.msgLabel}>&Omega;</span>}
    <div className={s.msgText}>{msg.text}</div>
  </div>
  // NEW — keep user messages as-is, replace omega messages with component:
  ```
  For omega messages use: `<OmegaMessage key={i} text={msg.text} />`
  For user messages keep the existing div structure unchanged.
- Replace the inline streaming div with: `<OmegaMessage text={streamingText} streaming />`
- Where `voiceState === 'processing'` shows thinking in the UI, replace with `<ThinkingIndicator />` component instead of just the streaming text (add it ABOVE the streaming text when voiceState is 'thinking' and streamingText is empty)

**Fix 2 — Replace inline Ω orb button with VoiceOrb component**
- Add import: `import VoiceOrb from '@/components/VoiceOrb/VoiceOrb';`
- Replace the entire `<button type="button" className={s.omegaWrapper} ...>` block (which contains omegaGlow, innerRing, omegaSymbol) with:
  ```jsx
  <VoiceOrb
    voiceState={voiceState}
    micLevel={0}
    ttsLevel={0}
    size={120}
    onClick={toggleListening}
  />
  ```
  Note: VoiceOrb doesn't have an onClick prop — wrap it in a button or div with the onClick. Check VoiceOrb's props at `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/components/VoiceOrb/VoiceOrb.tsx` first to see exact props. Wrap in: `<button type="button" onClick={toggleListening} aria-label="Toggle voice input" style={{background:'none',border:'none',cursor:'pointer',padding:0}}><VoiceOrb voiceState={voiceState} size={120} /></button>`

**Fix 3 — Add voice transcript confirmation**
- Add state: `const [heardText, setHeardText] = useState<string | null>(null);`
- In `recognition.onresult`, when transcript is captured (non-final), call `setHeardText(transcript.trim())` to show interim text
- When `isFinal` and sending, call `setHeardText(null)` to clear it
- In `recognition.onerror` and `onend`, call `setHeardText(null)`
- In the chat area JSX, just above the `<div ref={messagesEndRef} />`, add:
  ```jsx
  {heardText && (
    <div className={s.heardText}>
      <span className={s.heardLabel}>heard:</span> {heardText}
    </div>
  )}
  ```

**Fix 4 — Align VoiceState enum: rename processing → thinking, add followup and error**
- Change the local type: `type VoiceState = 'dormant' | 'listening' | 'thinking' | 'speaking' | 'followup' | 'error';`
- Find every usage of `'processing'` string in the file and change to `'thinking'`
- The stateClass computation at the bottom references `s.stateProcessing` — change to `s.stateThinking`
- In the status text display: change `voiceState === 'processing' ? 'Thinking...'` to `voiceState === 'thinking' ? 'Thinking...'`
- The `disabled={voiceState === 'processing'}` on buttons → change to `voiceState === 'thinking'`

Also add `.heardText` and `.heardLabel` to the CSS module. Read `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/app/tranquility/page.module.css` and append at the end:
```css
/* Voice transcript confirmation */
.heardText {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: rgba(180, 160, 255, 0.6);
  padding: 0.25rem 1rem;
  font-style: italic;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  animation: fadeIn 0.2s ease;
}
.heardLabel {
  color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.5);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  margin-right: 0.3rem;
}
```

Read all files before editing. Make all changes carefully. This is a Next.js TypeScript app — keep TypeScript valid.

